Concurrency: Concurrency is when two or more tasks can start, run, and complete in overlapping time periods.
It’s about managing multiple tasks at once.
async / await or Task, Await Task.WhenAll(tasks dowork);

Parallelism:Parallelism is when two or more tasks are executed at the same time on multiple CPU cores.
Using Parallel.For or Parallel.ForEach from System.Threading.Tasks.

The async and await keywords in C# make it easier to write asynchronous, non-blocking code . They are primarily used with Task and Task<TResult> to handle I/O-bound operations efficiently without freezing the main thread.
